WEBVTT

00:01.251 --> 00:02.628
Ray, taste this.
I don't want to taste it.

00:02.628 --> 00:04.755
No, you must, Ray, please, Ray.
I ‐‐ I have food of my own.

00:04.755 --> 00:06.882
Please, just for Mommy. Show Mommy.
Don't do this, don't make me do this.

00:06.882 --> 00:08.717
Come on, try a little bite.
One little bite for Mommy.
Don't make me.

00:08.717 --> 00:09.927
If you love me,
you'll taste a bite.

00:09.927 --> 00:11.011
Come on,
taste it, taste it.

00:11.011 --> 00:13.305
It's disgusting,
isn't it?

00:13.305 --> 00:14.723
Somebody said it.
I heard it, too.

00:14.723 --> 00:15.766
The word.

00:15.766 --> 00:18.227
Them.

00:18.227 --> 00:19.394
Who gets
to tell 'em off?

00:19.394 --> 00:20.854
Whoever finishes
their drink first.

00:23.524 --> 00:24.566
Come on, dude!

00:24.566 --> 00:26.818
Done! Whose booth?
<i>My</i> booth.

00:26.818 --> 00:29.279
Is this your first DiMeo
sensitivity speech?

00:29.279 --> 00:30.614
I'll do you proud.

00:33.450 --> 00:34.826
Why, hello there.

00:34.826 --> 00:36.787
Starting quiet, good.

00:36.787 --> 00:37.913
Get them to come to you.

00:37.913 --> 00:39.748
Ooh,
a little sass now.

00:39.748 --> 00:40.999
Making it his own.

00:40.999 --> 00:42.876
Wagging his finger ‐‐
Yeah, wish I had that.

00:42.876 --> 00:44.795
Yeah, that's right.
Hand in their face.

00:44.795 --> 00:46.755
They don't get to talk,
you get to talk.

00:46.755 --> 00:48.840
He's coming back,
efficient.

00:49.675 --> 00:51.134
[ Chuckles ]

00:51.134 --> 00:53.512
So, they're never gonna use
that word again, right?

00:53.512 --> 00:57.808
They're having their
driveway re‐tarred.

01:00.060 --> 01:02.604
Sorry.
Sorry!
So sorry about that.

01:07.526 --> 01:09.111
Who is this?

01:09.111 --> 01:11.613
No one told me Daniel Craig
uses a wheelchair,

01:11.613 --> 01:14.616
or that his best friend
was Mr. Ryan Gosling.

01:14.616 --> 01:16.577
Told you Mom
would think we look hot.

01:16.577 --> 01:18.745
JJ, I know you shot me down
when I offered

01:18.745 --> 01:20.289
to trick out your wheelchair
for prom

01:20.289 --> 01:22.291
with a special disco‐mode
option.

01:22.291 --> 01:23.875
I respect that.

01:23.875 --> 01:25.836
This button is party‐mode.

01:25.836 --> 01:27.963
"No, no, no, no!"

01:27.963 --> 01:29.339
Why not?

01:29.339 --> 01:32.134
"I get too much attention
at these things.

01:32.134 --> 01:34.136
I want to blend in."

01:34.136 --> 01:36.555
Well, good luck blending in,
'cause I'm afraid ‐‐

01:36.555 --> 01:38.432
boop, boop ‐‐

01:38.432 --> 01:40.767
your gorgeous‐mode buttons
still work.

01:40.767 --> 01:42.561
Mom,
you're embarrassing me!

01:42.561 --> 01:45.230
[ Giggling ]

01:45.230 --> 01:47.232
Darling, are you sure
you don't want Kenneth
to help you tonight?

01:47.232 --> 01:48.483
Kenneth: Oh, he won't need me
speaking for him.

01:48.483 --> 01:50.235
He won't be talking
much at all

01:50.235 --> 01:51.903
once he gets
to the bleachers.

01:51.903 --> 01:53.655
[ Laughs ]

01:53.655 --> 01:55.407
You know,
under the bleachers?

01:55.407 --> 01:59.036
Lafayette prom night?
It's make‐out city!

01:59.036 --> 02:00.912
Bone up on your French!

02:00.912 --> 02:02.706
Kissing, that is!

02:02.706 --> 02:04.374
I'll have
what they're having.

02:04.374 --> 02:05.500
[ Chuckles ]

02:05.500 --> 02:07.127
Who is this for?

02:07.127 --> 02:08.879
Oh, do seventh‐graders
go to prom now?

02:08.879 --> 02:10.589
I'm working refreshments.

02:10.589 --> 02:13.300
Now they tell me I'm just
lining up cups of punch.

02:13.300 --> 02:15.177
There's a month of studying
Tom Cruise in "Cocktail"

02:15.177 --> 02:17.638
I'll never get back.

02:17.638 --> 02:20.432
♪♪

02:29.066 --> 02:30.651
Dang!

02:30.651 --> 02:34.655
Ugh, balsamic vinegar
and egg nog?

02:34.655 --> 02:36.198
It's really more
about the throwing.
Yeah.

02:36.198 --> 02:39.201
♪♪

02:43.997 --> 02:46.124
Hey, aren't you the guy
that got stuck

02:46.124 --> 02:47.584
in the school mascot
costume?

02:47.584 --> 02:49.211
[ Laughs ]

02:49.211 --> 02:50.796
I'd like to think
of myself as the guy

02:50.796 --> 02:53.048
who got out of it.

02:55.092 --> 02:57.678
"Why is she smiling
at that?"

02:57.678 --> 02:59.262
I've heard about this.

02:59.262 --> 03:01.682
I think it's called
an aneurysm?

03:01.682 --> 03:03.100
I'm Riley Mullins.

03:03.100 --> 03:06.019
No, I've seen
Riley Mullins.

03:06.019 --> 03:09.022
I just had a bit of a makeover
over spring break.

03:09.022 --> 03:12.359
I lost the headgear
and got laser eye surgery.

03:12.359 --> 03:15.529
[ Whispering ] Dude, this is her
first day of being hot.

03:15.529 --> 03:17.614
She doesn't realize
she's out of you league.

03:17.614 --> 03:19.241
What's that?
Nothing.

03:19.241 --> 03:20.450
I'm the best you can do.
Let's go.

03:20.450 --> 03:21.910
[ Chuckles ]

03:21.910 --> 03:25.205
Well, I'm gonna go stand
behind a bar.

03:25.205 --> 03:29.167
"And I'm gonna go blend in
with an 800‐pound wheelchair."

03:29.167 --> 03:30.669
Good luck!

03:30.669 --> 03:34.131
♪♪

03:34.131 --> 03:36.007
You ready?

03:36.007 --> 03:38.093
Oh, sorry, JJ.

03:38.093 --> 03:39.594
Hey, everybody,
JJ's here.

03:39.594 --> 03:40.762
JJ selfie.

03:43.014 --> 03:46.143
Go, JJ, go, JJ!
Go, JJ!

03:46.143 --> 03:49.146
Make some room,
JJ dance circle!

03:49.146 --> 03:50.772
All: [ Chanting ]
Go, JJ! Go, JJ!

03:50.772 --> 03:53.108
Go, JJ! Go, JJ!

03:53.108 --> 03:55.026
Go, JJ!

03:55.026 --> 03:58.321
♪♪

03:58.321 --> 03:59.781
Why is that boy
staring at me?

03:59.781 --> 04:02.451
Ugh. He's just judging you
by your cover.

04:02.451 --> 04:05.412
Hey, she has a great
personality!

04:05.412 --> 04:08.123
It's so loud in here.

04:08.123 --> 04:10.542
We should go find
a quiet spot.

04:10.542 --> 04:12.919
Maybe...
under the bleachers?

04:12.919 --> 04:15.255
Oh, I don't know.

04:15.255 --> 04:17.424
I ‐‐ Apparently
at this school,

04:17.424 --> 04:20.051
"under the bleachers"
is kind of a thing.

04:20.051 --> 04:21.887
I know.

04:23.221 --> 04:25.599
All right, then.
[ Chuckles ]

04:25.599 --> 04:27.267
One moment, my lady.

04:29.227 --> 04:31.021
Quick question.
How do you make out?

04:31.021 --> 04:32.314
Think of your tongue
as a toothbrush

04:32.314 --> 04:33.940
and just brush her teeth.

04:33.940 --> 04:36.234
Thought so.
Thanks!

04:36.234 --> 04:37.694
What were you thinking,
giving me this?

04:37.694 --> 04:39.529
I was thinking
it was a nice gift.

04:39.529 --> 04:40.781
Don't worry. I won't make
that mistake again.

04:40.781 --> 04:42.532
[ Floor creaking ]

04:44.993 --> 04:47.871
Sorry, I‐I forgot this.

04:47.871 --> 04:50.165
Look, I know it's not my place,
but come on, guys.

04:50.165 --> 04:51.833
Don't argue.
Didn't you have plans?

04:51.833 --> 04:53.418
Go, you know, have fun.

04:53.418 --> 04:54.753
We are.
This is our night.

04:54.753 --> 04:55.462
Fight night.
It's the best!

04:55.462 --> 04:56.838
We don't like arguing
in front of the kids,

04:56.838 --> 04:58.381
so when we feel one coming on
we write it

04:58.381 --> 04:59.925
on a bit of paper
and we stuff it in the bottle.

04:59.925 --> 05:01.259
You have a night
all to yourselves,

05:01.259 --> 05:02.761
and that's how you choose
to spend it?

05:02.761 --> 05:05.222
Yeah, it's fun, isn't it?
Yeah, we yell, we throw things.

05:05.222 --> 05:07.516
Jimmy has this cute little vein
he pops out on his neck.

05:07.516 --> 05:09.226
Stop it. Your vein
is the cute one.
[ Giggles ]

05:09.226 --> 05:10.685
Here, I'll show you.
[ Clears throat ]

05:10.685 --> 05:12.521
How ungrateful
can you be?

05:12.521 --> 05:14.523
It was a gift
for no occasion.

05:14.523 --> 05:16.399
Oh no, the occasion was,
"Congratulations,

05:16.399 --> 05:18.068
your fingers are the size
of sausages."

05:18.068 --> 05:20.612
Have you see how big?
Size of a bloody napkin ring!

05:20.612 --> 05:23.073
What did I say?
A‐dorable.

05:23.073 --> 05:24.699
Uh...
Oh, don't judge us.

05:24.699 --> 05:26.117
Are you sure
you don't want me to?

05:26.117 --> 05:29.996
Because I am, and in this
argument, you're right.

05:29.996 --> 05:31.581
Do you know, I quite like
you being here, Kenneth.

05:31.581 --> 05:33.166
Would you like to stay and judge
the rest of our arguments?

05:33.166 --> 05:35.377
I don't what to say except...

05:35.377 --> 05:38.296
Judge Kenneth court
is now in session.

05:38.296 --> 05:41.091
♪♪

05:43.718 --> 05:46.513
"Hi. Are you okay?"

05:46.513 --> 05:49.015
No, my ex dumped me
three days ago,

05:49.015 --> 05:50.976
and now she's dancing
with some new guy.

05:50.976 --> 05:55.230
Ha, you've realized the truth
I've preached for millennia.

05:55.230 --> 05:56.648
Prom sucks.

05:56.648 --> 05:57.816
Caroline:
I'm with you.

05:57.816 --> 05:59.276
I can't believe
I thought I'd have fun.

05:59.276 --> 06:02.946
Now I'm stuck here
for three hours.

06:02.946 --> 06:06.032
"Why do we have
to stay here?"

06:06.032 --> 06:08.910
Ooh, a prom revolt!
I'm in.

06:08.910 --> 06:10.370
Are you in,
the tall girl?

06:10.370 --> 06:12.831
Oh, no. Is this some sort
of misfits

06:12.831 --> 06:14.124
coming together
kind of thing?

06:14.124 --> 06:17.377
Because I'm cool,
just FYI.

06:17.377 --> 06:19.796
Okay, she just
mimed spanking him. I'm in.

06:19.796 --> 06:22.299
"Let's get out of here."

06:22.299 --> 06:23.466
Lead the way.

06:23.466 --> 06:27.637
By the by, I am Erebus
of Nighthollow.

06:28.847 --> 06:30.515
You're not
gonna question that?

06:30.515 --> 06:31.725
This group is awesome!

06:31.725 --> 06:34.728
♪♪

06:34.728 --> 06:36.479
I have a confession.

06:36.479 --> 06:38.064
Oh, it's a prank.

06:38.064 --> 06:40.025
Lure me here
promising a kiss,

06:40.025 --> 06:42.986
then cue the guys in Reagan
masks throwing tomatoes.

06:42.986 --> 06:44.696
Fool me twice,
shame on Ray.

06:44.696 --> 06:47.365
No. Uh, the truth is,

06:47.365 --> 06:50.160
I didn't bring you
down here to talk.

06:53.163 --> 06:54.539
[ Notification beep ]

06:54.539 --> 06:56.166
Oh, I forgot!

06:56.166 --> 06:58.793
I'm spending the night at Lori's
and I forgot my backpack.

06:58.793 --> 07:00.837
My mom's outside with it.
Shoot.

07:00.837 --> 07:02.881
I'll be right back.

07:02.881 --> 07:05.717
Oh, she's perfect.

07:05.717 --> 07:06.968
I'm so sorry.

07:06.968 --> 07:09.054
I'm such a retard!

07:11.222 --> 07:13.642
Perfect may be
an overstatement.

07:13.642 --> 07:14.893
Young man:
Kiss or leave, nerd!

07:19.147 --> 07:21.024
Why be tied down, Curtis?
You're young.

07:21.024 --> 07:22.108
What are you,
a sophomore?

07:22.108 --> 07:24.402
I'm a junior.
Ooh, tick tock.

07:24.402 --> 07:26.071
Marry that chick.
Now scram.

07:26.071 --> 07:28.823
I've got customers.

07:28.823 --> 07:30.492
Hey, Ray.
Where's the girl?

07:30.492 --> 07:33.411
Riley? I'm gonna go back
and meet her in a second.

07:33.411 --> 07:34.829
Things are on track.

07:34.829 --> 07:37.624
I mean, there was one tiny thing
that kind of bumped me.

07:37.624 --> 07:39.501
What is the Reagan‐face
kids again?

07:39.501 --> 07:40.835
What? No!

07:40.835 --> 07:42.837
It was more like
she was being self‐deprecating,

07:42.837 --> 07:44.589
and then she used
this dumb word.

07:44.589 --> 07:46.132
She said...

07:46.675 --> 07:48.134
What?!

07:48.134 --> 07:49.135
Get over here!

07:49.135 --> 07:50.387
Stop,
that's not her!

07:50.387 --> 07:53.306
Well, she's here,
so she'll have to do.

07:53.306 --> 07:54.849
Ew,
who still says that?

07:54.849 --> 07:57.310
[ Growls ] I know!
I‐I hate her.

07:57.310 --> 08:00.605
Zero‐tolerance.
That is strike one.

08:00.605 --> 08:04.150
Don't. No, do not give her
a second chance.

08:04.150 --> 08:05.985
Stop convincing yourself that
that's okay.

08:05.985 --> 08:07.320
What would Mom say?

08:07.320 --> 08:09.864
She'd go off on her,
but she has that luxury.

08:09.864 --> 08:11.783
Mom's physically satisfied
by Dad.

08:11.783 --> 08:13.493
I don't have Dad.

08:13.493 --> 08:15.286
What happened to you,
man?

08:15.286 --> 08:16.871
Look, you know
I'm right, Ray.

08:16.871 --> 08:18.957
You can't let this go.

08:18.957 --> 08:21.251
Okay.
I'll tell her it's wrong.

08:21.251 --> 08:23.420
She'll see the light,
apologize,

08:23.420 --> 08:25.422
and then it's back to
"Who's your daddy".

08:25.422 --> 08:27.674
She is.

08:27.674 --> 08:29.259
You love him
because he's your brother.

08:29.259 --> 08:30.552
You love him
because he's your brother.

08:31.594 --> 08:33.596
I've reached my verdict.

08:33.596 --> 08:35.306
Jimmy does not have to hang out
with Maya's cousins.

08:35.306 --> 08:36.766
[ Gavel bangs ]
No!
Yes!

08:36.766 --> 08:38.893
Sorry Maya, I was really swayed
by Jimmy's point

08:38.893 --> 08:40.270
about how hard they suck.

08:40.270 --> 08:42.188
So hard!
Thank you!

08:43.606 --> 08:45.400
The fact that Maya would not be
able to keep a dog alive

08:45.400 --> 08:47.277
is not a reason
she shouldn't get one.

08:47.277 --> 08:48.862
The court rules Maya
can get a dog.

08:48.862 --> 08:51.865
Yes! I'm gonna have a dog
for a little bit.
Mnh.

08:51.865 --> 08:54.117
The court orders Jimmy
to be a more tender lover.

08:54.117 --> 08:55.660
Boo!
Ha, ha!
In your face.

08:55.660 --> 08:57.037
Boo!

08:57.037 --> 08:59.205
The court,
in its infinite wisdom,

08:59.205 --> 09:01.458
rules in favor of
myyyyy friend Jimmy.

09:01.458 --> 09:03.376
[ Gavel bangs ]
Yeah, I think you're
having a bit too much

09:03.376 --> 09:04.544
bloody fun with this.

09:04.544 --> 09:06.254
Is Kenneth
having too much fun?

09:06.254 --> 09:07.756
The court rules...no!

09:07.756 --> 09:09.966
[ Laughter ]

09:09.966 --> 09:13.094
Wow. This is like,
so much better.

09:13.094 --> 09:15.013
No one's asked me,
"How's the weather up there?"

09:15.013 --> 09:16.431
in almost five minutes.

09:16.431 --> 09:18.808
So, what's the plan, JJ?

09:18.808 --> 09:21.895
"Go hang out
somewhere else."

09:21.895 --> 09:24.606
I like it. We'll have
our own gathering.

09:24.606 --> 09:26.399
"Non‐prom!"
Yeah.

09:26.399 --> 09:28.985
You know, I didn't think
you guys were cool.

09:28.985 --> 09:31.738
But you kind of
became my best friends.

09:31.738 --> 09:33.656
"Feels fast for that."

09:33.656 --> 09:34.783
Yeah.
Yeah.

09:34.783 --> 09:36.910
Let's go.
[ Sighs ]

09:36.910 --> 09:39.037
[ Chanting "non‐prom" ]

09:39.037 --> 09:40.705
Non‐prom pride!

09:40.705 --> 09:43.291
We don't care
what anyone else thinks!

09:43.291 --> 09:45.460
All: [ Whispering ] Non‐prom.
Non‐prom.

09:45.460 --> 09:48.004
[ Whispering louder ]
Non‐prom. Non‐prom.

09:48.004 --> 09:51.633
Riley: Ray! I'm back here.
Follow the sound of my lips.

09:51.633 --> 09:54.761
[ Lips smacking ]
Man, this girl
has got it goin' on!

09:57.514 --> 10:01.559
Before we return
to the main event,

10:01.559 --> 10:03.144
I have something
to say.

10:03.144 --> 10:06.523
Earlier, a word was spoken
that kind of threw me.

10:06.523 --> 10:08.650
You said "retard."

10:08.650 --> 10:10.401
What? Uh‐‐ Oh.

10:10.401 --> 10:11.945
I didn't mean it
literally.

10:11.945 --> 10:13.446
I meant, like, "dumb."

10:13.446 --> 10:15.698
Oh. So you're sorry.
Great. Apology accepted.

10:15.698 --> 10:18.952
I wouldn't say I'm sorry.
I didn't intend it as offensive.

10:18.952 --> 10:20.912
It's not my fault that,
in today's culture,

10:20.912 --> 10:22.622
people get upset
by anything.

10:22.622 --> 10:24.332
Should we censor ourselves
simply because

10:24.332 --> 10:27.085
some unseen P. C. "they"
might get upset?

10:27.085 --> 10:29.420
That seems un‐American.

10:29.420 --> 10:31.422
Your argument
is so pretty.

10:31.422 --> 10:33.466
I'm captain
of the debate team.

10:33.466 --> 10:36.094
This is kind of my thing.

10:36.094 --> 10:38.930
[ Whispering ]
What's your counter‐argument?

10:38.930 --> 10:42.976
Uh...my family
gets really mad

10:42.976 --> 10:45.270
when they hear
that word.

10:45.270 --> 10:47.438
My brother
has cerebral palsy?

10:47.438 --> 10:49.524
I didn't know that.

10:49.524 --> 10:52.610
Does he have a developmental
disability as well?

10:52.610 --> 10:56.030
No. He ‐‐ He's cognitively
typical?

10:56.030 --> 10:58.199
Then that doesn't seem
to apply.

10:58.199 --> 11:00.535
But still.
My family says ‐‐

11:00.535 --> 11:03.288
But what do <i>you</i> think?

11:03.288 --> 11:08.543
I think I think what...
they think?

11:08.543 --> 11:09.586
I think.

11:09.586 --> 11:11.171
Consider my logic ‐‐

11:11.171 --> 11:13.798
"A," my intention
was benign,

11:13.798 --> 11:15.675
"B," language is
evolving,

11:15.675 --> 11:18.178
and "C,"
that's a good thing,

11:18.178 --> 11:21.556
as it robs a hurtful word
of its power.

11:21.556 --> 11:23.892
You really say
words good.

11:25.894 --> 11:27.604
You want to take
a quick five?

11:27.604 --> 11:30.315
All right. Sounds good.
Good call.

11:30.315 --> 11:33.860
I've never had teachers'
potato chips before.

11:33.860 --> 11:35.111
"They're better."

11:35.111 --> 11:36.863
[ Chuckles ]
They really are.

11:36.863 --> 11:40.074
"C‐plus"?!
C‐plus <i>this,</i> Mr. Leonards.

11:40.074 --> 11:42.493
JJ, you throw one hell
of a non‐prom.

11:42.493 --> 11:43.953
What else should we do?

11:43.953 --> 11:46.206
[ Gasps ] Ooh, maybe we could
put on some music?

11:47.624 --> 11:48.875
[ Beep ]
[ Upbeat music plays ]

11:48.875 --> 11:50.335
Oh, I love this song.

11:51.336 --> 11:53.004
Caroline,
Is there dancing at prom?

11:53.004 --> 11:54.005
Well, yeah, but ‐‐

11:54.005 --> 11:55.798
So there's no dancing
at non‐prom.

11:55.798 --> 11:58.801
JJ, permission to expel Caroline
from non‐prom?

12:00.261 --> 12:02.472
"I'm not your leader.

12:02.472 --> 12:04.432
And also,
permission denied."

12:04.432 --> 12:05.475
Damn it.

12:05.475 --> 12:06.643
Guys, it's okay.

12:06.643 --> 12:09.145
If music is that big
of an issue,

12:09.145 --> 12:12.106
I can just go hang out
by myself, I guess.

12:12.106 --> 12:13.650
That's very thoughtful of you,
Caroline.

12:13.650 --> 12:15.526
Goodbye!

12:16.569 --> 12:19.447
We found these fireworks
on a hike in the woods.

12:19.447 --> 12:22.283
I don't hate fun,
so I wanted to set them off.

12:22.283 --> 12:23.159
What's wrong with that?

12:23.159 --> 12:24.327
You were a father.

12:24.327 --> 12:26.746
And you were a mother,
but not mine!

12:26.746 --> 12:28.331
All right. All right.
I've heard enough.

12:28.331 --> 12:30.166
The court rules in favor
of Jimmy.

12:30.166 --> 12:31.459
Why?
Precedent.

12:31.459 --> 12:33.544
This court has been
consistently pro‐things

12:33.544 --> 12:35.880
that make loud noise
and are awesome.

12:35.880 --> 12:38.466
That is true.
Oh.
Bottle's empty.

12:38.466 --> 12:40.885
Time flies when you're screaming
at your wife for sport.

12:40.885 --> 12:42.762
Oh, no.
That can't be it.

12:42.762 --> 12:44.138
Fight about something else.
Come on.

12:44.138 --> 12:44.973
We've had our fun.

12:44.973 --> 12:46.599
Nah. Come on, Jimmy.

12:46.599 --> 12:48.268
But there's so much stuff
you haven't covered.

12:48.268 --> 12:49.852
The way she ‐‐
she always loses things.

12:49.852 --> 12:51.771
And ‐‐ and ‐‐ and ‐‐
and her lousy driving.

12:51.771 --> 12:54.315
Do I detect
a new opponent?

12:54.315 --> 12:55.483
Judge Jimmy.

12:55.483 --> 12:56.818
Do I get to use
Kenneth's gavel?

12:56.818 --> 12:59.862
I'd say so.

12:59.862 --> 13:01.406
I'll allow it.

13:01.406 --> 13:03.157
Let's do this thing.
Bring it on, Maya.

13:03.157 --> 13:04.951
Let's see what you got.

13:04.951 --> 13:06.869
Oh.
Yeah, I got one.

13:06.869 --> 13:11.666
You do sometimes help yourself
to our food a bit too readily.

13:11.666 --> 13:13.376
Oh! I see!

13:13.376 --> 13:15.420
'Cause your cooking
is such a prize?!

13:15.420 --> 13:16.587
Are you calling me fat?!

13:16.587 --> 13:18.047
No.
You know what?!
Burn in hell!

13:18.047 --> 13:19.841
Yo, I'm out of here!

13:20.967 --> 13:22.760
[ Door opens, slams ]

13:22.760 --> 13:24.804
Agh. That would've been
the perfect time to bang this.

13:25.805 --> 13:27.098
No. See?
Too late.

13:31.019 --> 13:32.770
She made some really
good points.

13:32.770 --> 13:35.106
She wants to kiss <i>you,</i> Ray.
How right can she be?

13:35.106 --> 13:36.649
"You guys see
a tall girl?"

13:36.649 --> 13:39.485
I mean, I guess I'm pretty tall.
What do you need?

13:39.485 --> 13:41.988
Wait. Actually. We need you
to weigh in on something.

13:41.988 --> 13:44.407
His little girlfriend
said the "R" word.

13:44.407 --> 13:46.701
Oh. I see.

13:46.701 --> 13:49.287
Just because JJ
has a disability,

13:49.287 --> 13:50.997
we should force him
to be arbiter

13:50.997 --> 13:52.749
of <i>all</i> things disability.

13:52.749 --> 13:54.167
Nice.

13:54.167 --> 13:55.918
Look who's
so sensitive now.

13:55.918 --> 13:59.130
A real champion
of the movement.

13:59.130 --> 14:00.465
He still wants
to kiss her.

14:00.465 --> 14:03.676
♪♪

14:06.220 --> 14:07.805
"Then kiss her."

14:07.805 --> 14:08.973
Really?
Really?

14:10.433 --> 14:14.353
"I hate that word,
but Ray deserves this one.

14:14.353 --> 14:16.439
He's a good brother.

14:16.439 --> 14:22.445
He has his whole life
to educate people.

14:22.445 --> 14:27.617
This is his one chance
to kiss a girl."

14:27.617 --> 14:29.952
Insulting,
but accurate.

14:29.952 --> 14:33.164
That's, like, the most generous
thing anyone's ever done for me.

14:33.164 --> 14:35.750
I'm gonna be kissing her,

14:35.750 --> 14:37.085
but I'm gonna
be thinking of you.

14:38.795 --> 14:40.630
So you got
your permission.

14:40.630 --> 14:43.966
It looks like the only
person left you need
to ask if it's okay...

14:43.966 --> 14:44.967
is you.

14:44.967 --> 14:46.177
Oh, let me check.

14:46.177 --> 14:48.012
Uh, he's good with it.

14:48.012 --> 14:50.306
[ Door opens, closes ]

14:50.306 --> 14:53.434
Sorry.
I... forgot my phone this time.

14:53.434 --> 14:55.186
Don't know what's happened
to my memory.

14:55.186 --> 14:57.772
Perhaps I've <i>eaten</i> it
like everything else.

14:57.772 --> 14:59.440
I didn't mean
any offense.

14:59.440 --> 15:01.734
I mean, you saw Jimmy and me
going back and forth.

15:01.734 --> 15:04.028
[ Sighs ] I‐I‐I think
it kicked up a few things

15:04.028 --> 15:05.530
that I've been feeling.

15:05.530 --> 15:07.198
Clearly, your situation
is different.

15:07.198 --> 15:09.534
You know
where you guys stand.

15:09.534 --> 15:12.036
But us ‐‐
Where are we going?

15:13.246 --> 15:15.289
Where are we?
What are we doing?

15:15.289 --> 15:18.376
I don't know.
I mean, uh...

15:18.376 --> 15:21.254
I thought we were just,
you know...

15:21.254 --> 15:23.172
A‐Are we really having
this conversation?

15:23.172 --> 15:24.507
Oh, you think it's early?

15:24.507 --> 15:26.134
Mm. It's not
a timing question.

15:26.134 --> 15:28.010
It's coming up on a year.
A great year.

15:28.010 --> 15:29.512
I mean,
we have a lot of fun.

15:29.512 --> 15:31.305
[ Scoffs ] "We have fun."

15:31.305 --> 15:33.850
This could all go away...
like that.

15:33.850 --> 15:36.352
JJ's last aide ‐‐
Oh. Yeah. I heard about her.

15:36.352 --> 15:38.604
That was different.
She's not you.

15:38.604 --> 15:40.189
Please.
Don't flatter me.

15:40.189 --> 15:42.900
I'm in this. Deep.

15:42.900 --> 15:47.488
And I'd like some reassurance
that you feel the same way.

15:47.488 --> 15:50.283
Uh, you know what?
Just... forget it.

15:50.283 --> 15:53.286
Kenneth.
You know, it all sounded
different in my head.

15:53.286 --> 15:54.620
I‐I should go.

15:54.620 --> 15:56.664
Oh, baby, no!
Come back!

15:57.957 --> 15:59.542
You been working
on your argument?

15:59.542 --> 16:01.210
Enough talk.

16:01.210 --> 16:03.045
Riley,
it's your lucky day.

16:03.045 --> 16:04.213
Take me.

16:05.798 --> 16:07.550
[ <i>Laughter</i> ]

16:07.550 --> 16:08.968
Dylan:
<i>Don't do it, Ray.</i>

16:08.968 --> 16:10.595
Ray: <i>Go away, Dylan.</i>

16:10.595 --> 16:12.722
Maya: <i>You really think</i>
<i>this is acceptable?</i>

16:12.722 --> 16:15.308
<i>You go away, too,</i>
<i>random British lady</i>
<i>who could be anyone!</i>

16:15.308 --> 16:16.684
<i>JJ okayed it.</i>

16:16.684 --> 16:18.436
Jimmy:
<i>Yes, JJ, who's intelligent</i>

16:18.436 --> 16:20.688
<i>and shouldn't be called ‐‐</i>
<i>No. It's not about JJ</i>

16:20.688 --> 16:22.607
<i>and that not being an accurate</i>
<i>description of him.</i>

16:22.607 --> 16:24.650
<i>What about people who do think</i>
<i>a different way</i>

16:24.650 --> 16:25.860
<i>or at a different pace?</i>

16:25.860 --> 16:27.945
<i>Should we reference them</i>
<i>in a nasty way</i>

16:27.945 --> 16:30.156
<i>when we do something dumb</i>
<i>'cause we think it's cute?</i>

16:30.156 --> 16:32.575
<i>Wait.</i>
<i>Am I forming my own opinion?</i>

16:32.575 --> 16:34.410
<i>Well, it's a hell</i>
<i>of a time to do that!</i>

16:34.410 --> 16:36.245
<i>Just kiss her.</i>
<i>She's so hot.</i>

16:36.245 --> 16:37.705
<i>Shut up.</i>
<i>You shut up.</i>

16:40.041 --> 16:42.126
Uhh. No!
I can't do it.

16:42.126 --> 16:45.046
Look,
what you said upset me.

16:45.046 --> 16:47.256
I was always told
that word was wrong,

16:47.256 --> 16:49.800
and ‐‐ and I never
thought about why.

16:49.800 --> 16:50.968
And now I have.

16:50.968 --> 16:54.764
So thanks...I guess.

16:54.764 --> 16:57.475
You can say whatever you want,
and that's cool,

16:57.475 --> 17:01.354
but no tongue that says
that word can brush my teeth.

17:01.354 --> 17:04.273
Wow.

17:04.273 --> 17:09.028
It's not the most logical
argument, but that passion ‐‐

17:09.028 --> 17:11.155
You really made me think.

17:11.155 --> 17:13.157
Then think.
I mean, we're in no rush.

17:13.157 --> 17:14.784
We got all the time
in the world.

17:14.784 --> 17:17.787
Are there any singles in here
lookin' to mingle? Whoa.

17:18.663 --> 17:21.040
Who are you?
Riley?

17:21.040 --> 17:22.416
I sit behind you
in science.

17:22.416 --> 17:24.377
Riley Mullins?

17:24.377 --> 17:26.629
You are crazy hot
with straight teeth.

17:26.629 --> 17:29.340
I am?
Uh... I guess.

17:29.340 --> 17:30.424
Does that matter?

17:30.424 --> 17:32.718
Come on.
My ex is three piles down.

17:32.718 --> 17:33.803
Let's go make out
next to her.

17:35.805 --> 17:38.224
Sorry, Ray.

17:38.224 --> 17:39.642
This just seems easier.

17:39.642 --> 17:42.895
If it helps,
you really made me think.

17:42.895 --> 17:44.564
It doesn't. At all.

17:44.564 --> 17:47.275
♪♪

17:50.987 --> 17:53.281
Oh. Hey.

17:53.281 --> 17:56.284
"For someone
who hates prom,

17:56.284 --> 17:58.494
you sure seem
to like it."

17:58.494 --> 18:00.746
[ Chuckles ]
I mean, yeah.

18:00.746 --> 18:02.456
I like the idea of it.

18:02.456 --> 18:04.250
I love dancing.

18:04.250 --> 18:06.294
I'm just kinda
self‐conscious.

18:06.294 --> 18:08.629
♪♪

18:08.629 --> 18:11.674
"Go.
It will be fun."

18:11.674 --> 18:13.676
[ Scoffs ] Well,
I don't see you in there.

18:14.552 --> 18:17.096
♪♪

18:17.096 --> 18:22.685
"Caroline, would you like to go
to prom with me?"

18:23.936 --> 18:25.313
[ Chuckles ]

18:25.313 --> 18:27.023
Okay.
W‐What is this?

18:27.023 --> 18:28.983
And why did Jimmy
have so many sleep masks

18:28.983 --> 18:30.276
for me to choose from?

18:32.403 --> 18:34.614
Kenneth, it would mean
the world to us

18:34.614 --> 18:37.366
if you would do us
the incredible honor

18:37.366 --> 18:39.619
of promising to be a part
of our family

18:39.619 --> 18:42.663
for a long, long time.

18:42.663 --> 18:46.334
I know we play a little
hard‐to‐get sometimes,

18:46.334 --> 18:47.835
but we've really
fallen for you.

18:47.835 --> 18:50.463
As a symbol
of our commitment,

18:50.463 --> 18:52.340
we'd like you
to have this thoughtful,

18:52.340 --> 18:54.425
but clearly man's,
ring.

18:57.053 --> 18:58.054
[ Gasps ]

18:58.054 --> 18:59.930
♪♪

18:59.930 --> 19:01.307
Huh. Cool.

19:01.307 --> 19:04.769
What? "Huh. Cool."
That's it?

19:04.769 --> 19:07.188
We just gave you
a fireworks proposal.

19:07.188 --> 19:08.898
How are you not
moved to tears?

19:08.898 --> 19:12.360
I mean...it's cute.

19:12.360 --> 19:15.154
But Jimmy [chuckles]
you were looking for an excuse

19:15.154 --> 19:16.364
to shoot off these fireworks.

19:16.364 --> 19:18.658
And you want to get rid
of this ring.

19:18.658 --> 19:19.950
Hang on.

19:19.950 --> 19:22.620
You barge in,
hijack our night,

19:22.620 --> 19:24.622
we bloody propose to you,

19:24.622 --> 19:27.958
and you can't even pretend
to be moved?

19:27.958 --> 19:32.213
I've waited 15 years
to set these suckers off.

19:32.213 --> 19:34.298
We finally do it,
in your honor,

19:34.298 --> 19:35.341
and I don't even
get to see them

19:35.341 --> 19:37.551
'cause I'm looking at
your unmoved face.

19:37.551 --> 19:40.429
Oh, look at you.
Veins poppin' out for me.

19:40.429 --> 19:42.264
Such irrational anger.

19:44.016 --> 19:45.393
I'm a DiMeo.

19:45.393 --> 19:47.144
Ugh, I'm going to bed.
Me too.
Give me this.

19:47.144 --> 19:49.939
[ Fireworks whistle, explode ]

19:49.939 --> 19:51.607
It fits.
[ Chuckles ]

19:51.607 --> 19:52.900
I accept!

19:52.900 --> 19:55.403
♪ When it drops, ooh ♪

19:55.403 --> 19:56.654
♪ I can't take my eyes
up off it ♪

19:56.654 --> 19:58.823
Hey, tall girl!
Hey, how's the weather up there?

19:58.823 --> 20:00.032
[ Laughter ]

20:00.032 --> 20:01.659
Hey. Get your head
out of the clouds.

20:01.659 --> 20:03.536
[ Laughs ]

20:03.536 --> 20:06.122
♪ And under the lights
when everything goes ♪

20:06.122 --> 20:07.998
I feel everyone's eyes
on me.

20:07.998 --> 20:10.751
♪ Nowhere to hide
when I'm getting you close ♪

20:10.751 --> 20:12.503
"Wait here."

20:12.503 --> 20:16.549
♪ When we move,
well, you already know ♪

20:16.549 --> 20:22.012
♪ So just imagine,
just imagine, just imagine ♪

20:22.012 --> 20:25.558
♪ Nothing I can see but you
when you dance, dance, dance ♪
Jimmy: <i>If you're hearing this...</i>

20:25.558 --> 20:26.871
♪ Feeling good, good,
creeping up on you ♪

20:26.871 --> 20:28.185
<i>... JJ has come to his senses</i>
<i>and hit the button.</i>

20:28.185 --> 20:30.354
♪ So just dance, dance, dance,
come on ♪
<i>Let's hear it!</i>

20:30.354 --> 20:32.106
♪ All those things
I shouldn't do ♪
All: JJ! JJ! JJ!

20:32.106 --> 20:34.567
♪ But you dance, dance, dance ♪
Dance circle!

20:34.567 --> 20:37.611
♪ And ain't nobody leaving soon,
so keep dancing ♪

20:37.611 --> 20:39.196
♪ I can't stop the feeling ♪

20:39.196 --> 20:40.364
♪ Got this feeling in my body ♪

20:40.364 --> 20:42.283
♪ So just dance, dance, dance ♪

20:42.283 --> 20:43.200
♪ I can't stop the feeling ♪

20:43.200 --> 20:44.326
♪ Got this feeling in my body ♪

20:44.326 --> 20:46.370
♪ So just dance, dance, dance ♪

20:46.370 --> 20:46.796
♪ Come on ♪

20:49.999 --> 20:51.000
Excuse me?

20:51.000 --> 20:51.834
Is this where

20:51.834 --> 20:53.043
I'm supposed to come

20:53.043 --> 20:53.794
for the free telescope giveaway?

20:53.794 --> 20:55.337
Hello?

20:57.298 --> 20:58.507
Oh, no. Not again.

20:58.507 --> 21:02.803
♪♪

21:02.803 --> 21:03.846
Damn it, Ray.

21:03.846 --> 21:04.722
When will you learn

21:04.722 --> 21:05.514
there's no such thing

21:05.514 --> 21:06.307
as a free telescope?

21:06.307 --> 21:07.433
Okay.

21:07.433 --> 21:09.185
Well played, Reagans.

21:09.185 --> 21:10.853
You guys ‐‐
You guys always find a way.

21:10.853 --> 21:12.772
All right. All right.
All right.

21:12.772 --> 21:14.565
You've had your fun now.

21:14.565 --> 21:16.108
Nice work.

21:16.108 --> 21:17.777
See ya next time.

21:17.777 --> 21:19.570
Missed. Missed.

21:19.570 --> 21:21.447
Missed. Missed me.
